Let's show support for the immediate rehabilitation & rebuilding of our dearly beloved UP School of Health Sciences. You can change your profile pic using this logo of SHS. Hope by simply doing this, we can catch the attention of the UP System.

What happened UP System? :(

The School of Health Sciences (SHS) was once hailed as the "heart & soul" of UP System, and that a "social conscience" college after its graduate doctors/nurses/midwives stay & work in the country especially in the most depressed, rural areas where community people see no doctor/health worker all their lifetime. 

Where most of the Filipino doctors or nurses go abroad (from the 60's up to the present times), UP-SHS graduates stay to fulfill the University's mandate of being the "University of the PEOPLE" (of the Filipino people), a university that cares in improving the health care system of the country.

More than ever, SHS needs your help. Until now, classes did not resume yet, for the school itself is 'beyond repair'. No classrooms, no faculty rooms, and even no decent boarding houses for the students. 

The local administration of SHS under the leadership of Dean Buddy Destura (a UP-SHS alumnus) is doing all its best to rebuild the school you dubbed as the "heart & soul" of UP. 

We call on our fellow alumni (from the entire UP system, here & abroad), all UP students & faculty concerned, and all Filipinos out there to help us rebuild UP-SHS once again. Helping SHS is "securing" that depressed, rural communities will have a health worker to attend to the health needs of the people.

2012 Freshie ako kaso nagLOA nung 1st sem (July 2012) kasi nagkaroon ako ng matinding sakit na naapektuhan talaga ang pisikal na itsura ko kaya kinailangan magLOA kung hindi lalala lalo. Nung nareadmit ako from LOA noong 1st sem 2013 (recovering pa from the illness), freshie standing ako kasi nga di ko naman nakumpleto yung units required para matawag na sophie. Kaya pag may nagtatanong kung anong year na ako, "dapat 2nd kaso freshie standing" ang lagi kong sinasabi. Isang bes, may Iska na nagsabi habang nakatingin sakin "Siya yung transferee." Siguro kasi freshie standing ako. Kumbaga "stereotyping." Dumiretso ako ng lakad na parang walang narinig. Pag naglalakad kasi ako nasa paglalakad ang focus ko kaya nung tumigil nako sa paglalakad saka ko lang naisip yung sinabi niya. Ang sakit lang kasi parang sinabi niya na di ako nakapasa ng UPCAT. Kwento ulit ng boss ko, dekada '70. UP Diliman.

Nagbarikada ang mga estudyante doon sa may area ng Checkpoint. Hapon na raw pero wala pang aksyon. Sinabihan niya mga kasama niya: 

(NV)

Bossing: i-abante na kaya natin 'yung barikada.

(Maraming pumayag na gawin 'yun, eh di inabante.  Lumipas ang ilang oras, wala pa ring nangyayari. Nainip na si Bossing. Dahil panganay siya sa kanila, siya rin pala ang inaasahang maghanda ng hapunan sa bahay nila. Tumingin sa relo, mamaya nagpaalam na sa kasamahan.)

Bossing: Alis na 'ko, wala namang nangyayari. Boring.

(At umuwi na nga siya sa kanila, naghanda na ng hapunan, pagkatapos ay binuksan ang TV para manood ng balita. Lumabas sa balita ang kaguluhang nangyayari sa UP Diliman. Nagkakagulo na sa pagitan ng mga taga-UP at ng mga pulis.)

Bossing: (pasigaw) Nandiyan ako kanina!

(Hindi niya napansin na dumating na pala ang tatay at nanay niya, dala pa ang mga bag pero nakatingin din sa TV.)

Daddy ni Bossing: Eh ano naman ang ginagawa mo doon kanina?

Bossing: (nagulat!) Napadaan lang po ako, Dad, nu'ng pauwi na ako.

Hindi niya binanggit na isa siya sa pasimuno doon. Bakit? Dahil ang kanyang Daddy ay assistant secretary sa Department of Education (o Ministry ba ang tawag noon?) Hehe... tapos Junior pa siya. Buti na lang daw nakaalis na siya. Iniisip pa lang niya 'yung maaring lumabas na balita kinikilabutan na siya:

"Kabilang sa mga nadakip na estudyante ay si ______ _______, Jr., anak ni Department (o Ministry) of Education assistant secretary ______ _______, Sr...."
Madalas ko tong ma-overhear sa UP. Diba? Diba? #Aminin #BeenThereDoneThat

Christmas season noon at madaming kids na nangangaroling sa loob ng campus. A kid asked me while I was sitting sa may DevCom sa Carabao Park... Nakasuot ako ng boots tapos red pants nun.. Medyo may kulay pa yung buhok..

Bata: Kuya Wyre ka ba? 
Me: Ah e, hindi e. Porma lang 'to.
Bata: Anong pangarap mo?

Nagulat ako... Hindi ko alam isasagot ko...

Me: I want to be a professor, teacher ng mga college students. Ikaw? 
Bata: Gusto ko maging abogado, nakakulong kasi tatay ko. Gusto ko siya ilabas sa kulungan kaso wala kaming pera. Napagkamalan siyang magnanakaw nung pinagtatrabahuhan niya.
Me: Ilan kayong magkakapatid?
Bata: Lima, ngayon tatlo na lang.
Me: Bakit? Anong nangyari?
Bata: Namatay kasi yung kakambal ko nung baby pa lang kami. Tapos yung kuya ko, nabundol ng kotse.
Me: Ay, ganun ba.. nakakalungkot naman. Nasan yung nanay mo?
Bata: Nasa bahay, inaalagaan yung kapatid ko.. may sakit kasi.

Hindi ko alam kung ano mafefeel ko that time, ramdam ko kasi yung agony nung bata. Pero ayun, naglalaro siya kasama yung mga kaibigan niya at kumakanta ng mga carols sa mga nakaupo. Bigla kong natanong...

Me: San mo gusto mag aral ng college?
Bata: Dito siyempre sa UP.
Me: Aral kang mabuti ha? Gusto ko after 10 years, makikita kita dito sa UP.

Binigyan ko siya ng pera tapos sabi ko bigyan nya ako ng joke every night noon, pero hindi ko na siya nakita dun ulit. Sana okay lang siya. Sana makapasok din siya sa UP.

Sa may pancit canton-an sa Vinzons, si Nestor, Angelica at Ako, kausap iyong baklang bata na nanglilimos sa campus.

Ako: San mo gustong mag-aral, papag-aralin kita?
Bata: Sa Ateneo...
Ako: Bakit naman? Ayaw mo ba sa UP?
Bata: AYAW KO, MARAMING MANGHIHINGI NG BARYA SA AKIN...

Tawanan kami, pati iyong kumakain na ate. Hahaha. Di ko alam kung saan niya nakuha iyong lohika niya. Ayaw niyang mahingian ng barya samantalang iyon din naman ang kinabubuhay niya.

I don't know if I should really share this but since it's almost Valentine's Day, i-share ko na din since if not for UP, this story will never happen.

2nd Semester 2006-2007, OF ako na ako ng time na to. Sa UPB talaga dapat ako papasok pero since taga LB naman ako, nakipagsapalaran na ako na magwaitlist sa UPLB at un, sinuwerte nman ako. Pero yung swerteng yun, wala pa pala sa swerteng mararanasan ko sa UPLB.

Nakaregister ako sa SOSC2 Class, kay Ma'am Ajoc na maganda ang hair, sa CAS OUR Room(???- Not sure kung un nga tawag dun), T-TH and sched 11:30-1:00. Pagpasok ko, wala akong kilala maliban sa sis ko sa SAM-UP so dun ako tumabi sa kanya so feel ko hindi na ako OP. May kakilala na ako. Sa harap namin, may 2 babaeng nakaupo na prang freshie din. Every meeting halos pareho pareho lang, kunyaring nakikinig, tawa sa instructor tpos alis na after class . Minsan nasisilip ko ung desk nung isang girl sa harap ko. Magaling magdrawing then nakita ko din ung mga assignements niya so may idea ako ng subjects na kinukuha niya. 

Isang araw ewan kung bakit pero maaga akong pumasok, wala pang 1130 nasa klase na ako. Wala pa yung sis ko so mejo nabagot ako. Nung time na un andun na yung 2 babae sa harap ko, ready for class na. Naging friendly ako so eto yung naging convo namin. (non-verbatim)

Me: Kumukuha ka ba ng NASC6?( since nakita ko ung assignment niya previously)

G1: Ah oo. Subject ko un ngayon.

Me: May kilala ka bang ***?(Name nung crush ko nung time na un since un din ung subject niya at that time.)

G1: Wala eh.

Blah blah blah

Long story short, i was talking to Girl1 the whole time and then Girl2 was in the convo too but she only uttered 3 words...

 "HA HA HA"

Nakitawa lang xa during our convo.

And those three words became the start of everything. After ng sem I found Girl2's friendster account so i added her. not caring about the who's viewed me function, i stalked her FS account and told to myself, "Ang ganda pala nito. Sayang, sana kinausap ka to dati lagi." And instantly I had a crush on her.

In four years sa UPLB, i only saw here twice except those times we were in class.(though the words ha ha ha were the only words she ever gave me)

Once sa jeep where i was able to get her number after like a year from being classmates that in the end she hated me dahil sa sobrang papansin ko sa kanya, nainis xa na hindi na xa nagreply at talagang sinungitan niya ako. she then became one of those girls na "Pangarap na lang".

Then again, nakita ko siya sa opening tambayan namin sa MB na invited xa since housemate niya ung president namin at that time.

I took those three convesations with me through time but not like i was deeply in love with her but i never forgot everything about her. 

And seven years later since the first time I heard her voice, now i keep hearing it everyday. From the 3 words HA HA HA, now I'm hearing "I love you." I was nothing to her at that time that she even forgot how we met and now we are about to celebrate our first anniversary.

This might not be a really good story since i don't wanna put a lot of details coz somethings are better to be understood between the two of us. I just want to share it because every decision i made from when i was in HS, to go to UPLB and up to this day brought me to this place to where i am, to this happiness. From 7 years me who only saw her as an impossible girl to get, to the me now who sees her as the best girl I could ever have. This is not something I want to share because i want to make kilig moments for me and gather some likes, i just want to share this and to let everyone know that everything is possible, that the person you thought you could only wish for can be yours, that someone is really out there that would make all those cheesy lines real, that all the love songs that you used to quote are now applicable to you, that waiting really is worth it coz it happened to me and it all started at a simple laugh in UPLB.

UP COLLEGE OF DENTISTRY
Frequently Asked Questions

(aka "Yung mga sagot na paulit-ulit ko nang tinatype sa cellphone, I should have them saved to my Templates already".)

Q: Pwede ba po magpa-braces?
A: Pwede po! Unfortunately, wala po akong kilala talaga sa postgrad (Ortho) department, so I can't give you much information about that. Also, mahaba-haba na po ang waiting list for new patients...

Q: Magkano estimated for crown/bridge/dentures?
A: As it's written po sa service menu that was posted, there is a set price (for the materials that WE use IN THE SCHOOL) plus a varying price for the lab fee. The lab fee will depend on the material to be used by the lab (to be collectively determined by your needs/requests and the clinician's judgment) and the lab that your attending clinician chooses. Hindi po ako makakapagbigay ng reliable estimate kasi HIGHLY varied po ang fees ng iba't ibang labs. They can range from as low as 200 to as high as 3000.

Q: Pwede po magpasched?
A: Unless you have a referral slip from another dentist, I cannot know specifically what your treatment needs are, and thus it will be hard for me to refer you to a clinician for scheduling on your FIRST visit. May requirements po kasi kami, and while we're not strictly limited to fulfilling only those requirements, admittedly we want to concentrate first on which ones we still need to fulfill before taking on any extra cases. If you are a first-time patient with no attending clinician yet, the best thing to do is to come to UP by 8am/1pm to register for diagnosis. After your first chart is completed, only then will we be able to set schedules for your treatment.

Q: May makakagawa na po ba pagdating ko?
A: Again, it depends on what treatment you need. We cannot guarantee that there will be clinicians available to take your case upon your arrival. Minsan meron, pero most of the time wala kasi may mga naka-sched na po kami na patients of our own. So sana po maintindihan ninyo that we might not be able to attend to you immediately once you've been diagnosed, and sana hindi na po kayo maging sobrang demanding to the point na ang mga prof na po namin mismo yung nagagalit sa potential patients kasi unreasonable po yung gusto niyong mangyari.
-- Corollary: Kung hindi po kayo makakarating, PLEASE inform your clinician as early as possible. A huge factor sa pagkadelay ng graduation is because of requirements that aren't completed due to patients' non-compliance with their scheduled appointments. Nagtatabi po kami ng mga half-day/whole day for you, hindi kami nagsisingit basta-basta ng ibang pasyente unless we're absolutely sure that that schedule is free. So please, sana respetuhin niyo rin po ang oras namin. Kung hindi kayo dadating, sabihan kami agad para makapaghanap kami ng ibang pasyente at hindi nasasayang ang mga half-day namin na palibot-libot lang na walang ginagawa. :)

Q: Matagal ba ang treatment?
A: Sa isang salita -- oo. Bakit? Nagpapacheck po kasi kami, and every step ang kailangan ipa-check. Minsan matagal bago macheckan kasi madami kaming nagpapacheck sa kakaunting prof, minsan busy ang profs, minsan nawawala ang profs kasi may klase sa preclinical subjects or may urgent matters to attend to or nakikipag-chikahan pa (:PPPPP)... And bago kami mag-umpisa ng trabaho, nagkakaroon pa muna ng mini-discussion about the case, unlike some other schools na basta sinasabi lang ng mga prof is "Okay" and nag-uumpisa na sila agad (I witnessed this for myself).

Q: Ga'no katagal matapos ang root canal / bridges / dentures / *insert other multiple-visit procedures here*?
A: That will depend on your compliance with your schedule. We start by doing work-ups of your case (pictures, impression, history taking, etc), which will take half a day. Then there's case discussion with a prof, and that WILL take multiple sessions. (Our profs want to make sure we know what we're doing before we even start doing anything. You understand.) Please remember that yours is not the only case we are handling -- we have several requirements that all need our attention equally. 
-- Corollary: Tumatagal po ang trabaho pag nala-late kayo. Obviously :) So please come on time.

Q: Pwede magpasched on Wednesday?
A: Unless your appointment is for complete or removable partial dentures, then no. :)
